  "articleSummary": "This technical tutorial provides a comprehensive guide to securing self-hosted Docker environments on both home networks and public VPS instances. The author argues that security is the administrator's sole responsibility and advocates for a defense-in-depth approach covering image versioning, secrets management, and network hardening. Key technical recommendations include pinning specific image tags instead of using `:latest`, implementing runtime secret validation, and utilizing tools like Nginx proxies and canary tokens. The tone is practical and encouraging, aimed at hobbyists and developers who need to balance system stability with robust protection against unauthorized access.",
